Gold Fields, Investec and Merafe Could Move: South African Stocks Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-04-14T02:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/gold-fields-investec-and-merafe-could-move-south-african-stocks-preview.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
advanced 113.92, or 0.4 percent, to 32,353.79 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)  : Africa’s second-biggest gold
producer publishes its mineral resource and reserve statement.
The stock rose 36 cents, 0.3 percent, to 121.61 rand.  Investec Property Fund Ltd. (IPF SJ): The property
investment company, a unit of Investec Plc, a South African
private bank and wealth manager, begins trading on the
Johannesburg bourse.  Invicta Holdings Ltd. (IVT)  : The seller of ball bearings
and engineering equipment said it has entered into talks with
co-shareholder aloeCap (Pty) Ltd. over a possible restructuring
of the latter’s 20 percent stake in Humulani Investments (Pty)
Ltd., an Invicta subsidiary. The talks may affect the share
price of Invicta, which was unchanged at 44 rand.  Merafe Resources Ltd. (MRF)  : The part owner of the
world’s biggest ferrochrome producer holds a  shareholders’
meeting . Merafe increased 3 cents, or 1.9 percent, to 1.58 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
